                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#37r" facs="037"/><desc>Two <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1041HolyMen"/></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#37v" facs="038"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/>, <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/> and John stand beside the <term key="cross"/></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#75r" facs="075"/><desc>An <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1012Equestrian"/> spears a figure</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#75v" facs="076"/><desc> Two <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1041HolyMen"/></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#106r" facs="107"/><desc>Crude drawing in blue ink</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#112r" facs="112"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1049Resurrection"/>, raising <persName ref="PRS1386Adam"/> and <persName ref="PRS3926Eve"/> from the dead</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#112v" facs="113"/><desc><ref type ="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/> <name ref="PRS4306GabraMa"/> with lions and leopards</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d13">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#5r #10r #14v #20r #71r #80r" facs="005 010 015 020 071 080"/> (secondary ornamental band);
                  <locus target="#23v #99r" facs="024 099"/> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#34r #44v #52v #56r #64v #74r #114v" facs="034 045 053 056 065 074 115"/> (line of black dots);
                  <locus target="#86v #106r" facs="087 106"/> (multiple full stops and lines of alternating red and black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                      Throughout the book, the word ʿhereʾ (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝየ፡</foreign>) marks every tenth line, as though an audit of the strophes were being performed
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                      A later hand has written on folios throughout the codex in blue ink. Mentions several people, such as Gäbrä Mädḥǝn (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ መድሕን፡</foreign>) on <locus target="#1r" facs="001"/> and Wäldä Gäbrǝʾel (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡</foreign>) on <locus target="#2r" facs="002"/>
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                      Additional headings have been added for several of the first 28 Psalms (e.g., <locus target="#5r #5v #6v" facs="005 006 007"/>)
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#39v" facs="040"/>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is not marked
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#106r" facs="106"/>
                    note of secondary ownership in an untrained hand. The name of the owner is unclear
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#14r #19r #20v #27r #31r" facs="014 019 021 027 031"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#105v" facs="106"/>);
                      text has been removed (<locus target="#5r #7r #7v #9r #9v" facs="005 007 008 009 010"/>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
